&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The maternity unit at Guy&#39;s and St Thomas&#39; NHS Foundation Trust are looking to recruit 1.6 FTE AFC Band 6 midwives to join our friendly and supportive team on our private maternity ward - Westminster Suite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Westminster Suite is our obstetric-led private maternity ward providing antenatal, intpartum and postnatal care. This role includes all aspects of midwifery care for women booking into private obstetric care. The team works days, nights and weekends. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: &lt;/strong&gt;15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview and Assessment:&lt;/strong&gt; 26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJemima DokuJob titleMidwifery Practice LeaderEmail addressJemima.Doku@gstt.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are ready for the challenge and would like a change contact Postnatal Matron and Westminster Suite Matron, Camella Main, Tel. 020 7188 8685 or email camella.main@gstt.nhs.uk if you wish to discuss further.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
